response: "{ \"title\": \"Elegant Enclosure\", \"description\": \"A rectangular garden has an area of 120 square meters and a perimeter of 44 meters. Find the dimensions of the garden.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef find_garden_dimensions(area: int, perimeter: int) -> tuple:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `area` (int): The area of the rectangular garden in square meters.\\n- `perimeter` (int): The perimeter of the rectangular garden in meters.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns a tuple `(width, height)` representing the dimensions of the garden.\", \"code\": \"import math\\ndef find_garden_dimensions(area: int, perimeter: int) -> tuple:\\n    if area <= 0 or perimeter <= 0:\\n        raise ValueError('Invalid input')\\n    length = perimeter / 2\\n    width = math.sqrt(length**2 - (area/length))\\n    return int(width), int(math.ceil(length))\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert find_garden_dimensions(120, 44) == (10, 12)\", \"assert find_garden_dimensions(-1, 0) == ValueError('Invalid input')\"] }"
